which was Steven
Greer's attempt,

00:46:04.720 --> 00:46:07.080 align:middle line:84%
just bring the experts in,
let them tell what they saw.

00:46:07.080 --> 00:46:07.880 align:middle line:90%
You're there.

00:46:07.880 --> 00:46:08.770 align:middle line:90%
You've vetted them.

00:46:08.770 --> 00:46:10.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And a dead silence
on the part of the media.

00:46:10.530 --> 00:46:11.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Dead silence.

00:46:11.430 --> 00:46:12.490 align:middle line:90%
And I mean, I was there--

00:46:12.490 --> 00:46:13.650 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And no congressmen
wanted to talk about it.

00:46:13.650 --> 00:46:15.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No one
wanted-- and these guys,

00:46:15.030 --> 00:46:16.863 align:middle line:84%
I mean some of these
older men in particular

00:46:16.863 --> 00:46:20.240 align:middle line:84%
who had been holding on through
their national security oaths,

00:46:20.240 --> 00:46:21.080 align:middle line:90%
were in tears.

00:46:21.080 --> 00:46:23.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was very challenging
for them to tell the story.

00:46:23.660 --> 00:46:26.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: And I had agreed
to represent any of them

00:46:26.240 --> 00:46:29.500 align:middle line:84%
if they tried to
revoke their pensions

00:46:29.500 --> 00:46:31.950 align:middle line:84%
or tried to prosecute them
for a violation of security

00:46:31.950 --> 00:46:32.750 align:middle line:90%
clearance.

00:46:32.750 --> 00:46:34.966 align:middle line:84%
I had agreed to represent
them individually.

00:46:34.966 --> 00:46:37.590 align:middle line:84%
So that's how we got a number of
them to come forward and talk.

00:46:37.590 --> 00:46:38.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they
were still scared.

00:46:38.750 --> 00:46:39.070 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Oh, yeah.

00:46:39.070 --> 00:46:41.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the point is we
did have a public disclosure.

00:46:41.980 --> 00:46:43.410 align:middle line:90%
It went nowhere, OK?

00:46:43.410 --> 00:46:45.740 align:middle line:84%
So now we have this
very deep dialogue

00:46:45.740 --> 00:46:47.380 align:middle line:90%
that you're developing.

00:46:47.380 --> 00:46:49.370 align:middle line:84%
And you and I talked
off camera about this,

00:46:49.370 --> 00:46:51.180 align:middle line:90%
and I saw it for myself.

00:46:51.180 --> 00:46:55.870 align:middle line:84%
I was at a Buddhist retreat
at a monastery recently,

00:46:55.870 --> 00:46:58.600 align:middle line:84%
and I ran into a
scientist from JPL.

00:46:58.600 --> 00:47:00.907 align:middle line:84%
She said, oh, well, I'm
just contracting right now.

00:47:00.907 --> 00:47:01.990 align:middle line:90%
I'm not working full time.

00:47:01.990 --> 00:47:03.080 align:middle line:90%
I said, what are you on?

00:47:03.080 --> 00:47:08.060 align:middle line:84%
She said, well, they've given me
some of the samples from Mars,

00:47:08.060 --> 00:47:10.310 align:middle line:84%
and we're looking to see
if it's possible there's

00:47:10.310 --> 00:47:11.974 align:middle line:90%
any life on Mars.

00:47:11.974 --> 00:47:13.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: Microscopic life.

00:47:13.140 --> 00:47:14.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Microscopic
life on Mars.

00:47:14.690 --> 00:47:16.770 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, oh,
gosh, here we go.

00:47:16.770 --> 00:47:19.300 align:middle line:84%
And you and I talked
off camera, and if you

00:47:19.300 --> 00:47:23.920 align:middle line:84%
will explain to people how
the public disclosure is

00:47:23.920 --> 00:47:25.510 align:middle line:90%
going to likely roll out.

00:47:25.510 --> 00:47:27.540 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to be
another big event.

00:47:27.540 --> 00:47:30.920 align:middle line:84%
The big events have occurred,
and it went nowhere.

00:47:30.920 --> 00:47:34.055 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I believe that
what's happening now--

00:47:34.055 --> 00:47:36.420 align:middle line:84%
and there's two parts
to this answer, I said.

00:47:36.420 --> 00:47:39.440 align:middle line:84%
One of them is that now
that these planets are being

00:47:39.440 --> 00:47:41.420 align:middle line:84%
discovered, what they're
going to be doing

00:47:41.420 --> 00:47:43.040 align:middle line:84%
is they're going
to say, oh, look,

00:47:43.040 --> 00:47:45.940 align:middle line:84%
we've discovered a planet
that has a sea of ice,

00:47:45.940 --> 00:47:49.230 align:middle line:84%
and we've now discerned
microscopic life

00:47:49.230 --> 00:47:51.230 align:middle line:90%
beneath the surface of this ice.

00:47:51.230 --> 00:47:53.290 align:middle line:84%
And so they're going to
break that to begin with.

00:47:53.290 --> 00:47:53.850 align:middle line:90%
Then they're going to say--

00:47:53.850 --> 00:47:54.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Water.

00:47:54.660 --> 00:47:57.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Water
and microscope life.

00:47:57.090 --> 00:48:03.070 align:middle line:84%
And now we've discovered life
in the seas of another planet.

00:48:03.070 --> 00:48:07.190 align:middle line:84%
We've discovered very
primitive reptiles and stuff

00:48:07.190 --> 00:48:08.170 align:middle line:90%
on another planet.

00:48:08.170 --> 00:48:11.109 align:middle line:84%
We've discovered mammalian
life on some other planet.

00:48:11.109 --> 00:48:12.650 align:middle line:84%
And they're eventually
going to get--

00:48:12.650 --> 00:48:13.910 align:middle line:84%
they're just going
to feather it in one

00:48:13.910 --> 00:48:15.600 align:middle line:84%
step at a time like
this, and they're

00:48:15.600 --> 00:48:18.320 align:middle line:84%
going to ultimately say, oh,
we've discovered some extremely

00:48:18.320 --> 00:48:22.180 align:middle line:84%
primitive life form,
like Cro-Magnon life

00:48:22.180 --> 00:48:24.610 align:middle line:84%
forms like that, whether
they're reptilian or mammalian

00:48:24.610 --> 00:48:25.860 align:middle line:90%
or whatever they are.

00:48:25.860 --> 00:48:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And what they're
going to do is they've

00:48:27.580 --> 00:48:28.470 align:middle line:90%
decided to feather it in.

00:48:28.470 --> 00:48:29.344 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Spoon-feed.

00:48:29.344 --> 00:48:33.330 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Feather in to the
world public the existence,

00:48:33.330 --> 00:48:36.380 align:middle line:84%
eventually, of a more
sophisticated civilization.

00:48:36.380 --> 00:48:38.110 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to
keep secret the fact

00:48:38.110 --> 00:48:40.600 align:middle line:84%
that they know that there's
a very highly technologically

00:48:40.600 --> 00:48:43.426 align:middle line:84%
developed civilization that's
actually been coming here.

00:48:43.426 --> 00:48:45.300 align:middle line:84%
And they're just going
to blow right by this.

00:48:45.300 --> 00:48:47.640 align:middle line:84%
But second part of
the answer to that

00:48:47.640 --> 00:48:50.950 align:middle line:84%
question about disclosure--
and this Randy Koppang.

00:48:50.950 --> 00:48:54.730 align:middle line:84%
Randy Koppang, who has been to
every single UFO conference,

00:48:54.730 --> 00:48:57.010 align:middle line:84%
has got copies of every
single speech that's

00:48:57.010 --> 00:49:00.010 align:middle line:84%
ever been given, he said, look,
when you really look at this,

00:49:00.010 --> 00:49:02.290 align:middle line:84%
they're engaged in a
disclosure project.

00:49:02.290 --> 00:49:03.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's already-- yeah.

00:49:03.540 --> 00:49:05.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: They are engaged
in disclosure project.

00:49:05.960 --> 00:49:06.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:49:06.130 --> 00:49:08.213 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: They are
feathering in this information

00:49:08.213 --> 00:49:10.020 align:middle line:84%
to different people,
including journalists,

00:49:10.020 --> 00:49:11.880 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE] and others.

00:49:11.880 --> 00:49:13.240 align:middle line:90%
And they're giving them access.

00:49:13.240 --> 00:49:15.230 align:middle line:84%
There's people from
Area 51 that are

00:49:15.230 --> 00:49:17.670 align:middle line:84%
being allowed to come out
and talk to people in public.

00:49:17.670 --> 00:49:19.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Nick Pope and the
whole English story, yeah.

00:49:19.510 --> 00:49:20.509 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:49:20.509 --> 00:49:22.100 align:middle line:90%
They're allowed to come out.

00:49:22.100 --> 00:49:25.026 align:middle line:84%
And he said, and Randy is
writing a book about this

00:49:25.026 --> 00:49:26.150 align:middle line:90%
now, saying, wait a second.

00:49:26.150 --> 00:49:30.020 align:middle line:84%
Don't you realize that there is
a disclosure project going on?

00:49:30.020 --> 00:49:31.825 align:middle line:84%
It's just taking an
entire generation.

00:49:31.825 --> 00:49:32.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's perpetual.

00:49:32.190 --> 00:49:32.620 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:49:32.620 --> 00:49:35.078 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That they're going
to take the entire generation

00:49:35.078 --> 00:49:38.702 align:middle line:84%
from 1947 with the Roswell
encounter all the way through.

00:49:38.702 --> 00:49:41.160 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to have an
entire generation that they're

00:49:41.160 --> 00:49:45.000 align:middle line:84%
planning like 100-year rollout
of more and more information

00:49:45.000 --> 00:49:47.570 align:middle line:84%
to the point where
this generation passes

00:49:47.570 --> 00:49:50.100 align:middle line:84%
from the scene, but
the new generation

00:49:50.100 --> 00:49:53.820 align:middle line:84%
is coming in behind us are
completely acclimated to this.

00:49:53.820 --> 00:49:56.410 align:middle line:84%
Because you take the millennial
generation that are basically

00:49:56.410 --> 00:50:05.030 align:middle line:84%
33 down to about 15 right now,
that millennial generation.

00:50:05.030 --> 00:50:08.276 align:middle line:84%
You poll them, and 95%
of them will tell you

00:50:08.276 --> 00:50:09.900 align:middle line:84%
that it's absolutely
clear that there's

00:50:09.900 --> 00:50:11.410 align:middle line:90%
extraterrestrial intelligence.

00:50:11.410 --> 00:50:15.310 align:middle line:84%
And not only that, but it's very
likely that these UFOs and ET

00:50:15.310 --> 00:50:17.380 align:middle line:90%
contacts are happening.

00:50:17.380 --> 00:50:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And so this second answer
to the question is,

00:50:21.050 --> 00:50:22.670 align:middle line:90%
there's already a rollout.

00:50:22.670 --> 00:50:25.330 align:middle line:90%
This is going on here, OK?

00:50:25.330 --> 00:50:28.020 align:middle line:84%
But they're going to go
this other route of doing it

00:50:28.020 --> 00:50:29.270 align:middle line:90%
kind of formally.

00:50:29.270 --> 00:50:30.920 align:middle line:84%
But this other one
is kind of informal.

00:50:30.920 --> 00:50:33.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: For the early adopters
that are willing to listen.

00:50:33.420 --> 00:50:34.550 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's right.

00:50:34.550 --> 00:50:36.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Do you
think-- and this

00:50:36.070 --> 00:50:37.910 align:middle line:84%
is the big question
I think everybody

00:50:37.910 --> 00:50:40.650 align:middle line:84%
in this particular area
of study has asked.

00:50:40.650 --> 00:50:46.360 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that the incredible
caution has been justified,

00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:50.670 align:middle line:84%
that the public at large really
isn't capable of handling this

00:50:50.670 --> 00:50:52.680 align:middle line:84%
if it were something
to happen very quickly?

00:50:52.680 --> 00:50:53.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: No, no.

00:50:53.840 --> 00:50:54.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I don't either.

00:50:54.480 --> 00:50:56.521 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: I think there
are two answers to this.

00:50:56.521 --> 00:50:57.984 align:middle line:90%
It's not because of the public.

00:50:57.984 --> 00:50:59.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What are
they concerned about?

00:50:59.650 --> 00:51:02.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I know there's whole
technology part of the story.

00:51:02.520 --> 00:51:03.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: That's the first one.

00:51:03.010 --> 00:51:04.866 align:middle line:84%
Remember during the
Cold War, during that

00:51:04.866 --> 00:51:06.240 align:middle line:84%
entire period--
remember the Cold

00:51:06.240 --> 00:51:07.950 align:middle line:90%
War went all the way from 1917.

00:51:07.950 --> 00:51:09.920 align:middle line:90%
It didn't just begin at 1945.

00:51:09.920 --> 00:51:12.240 align:middle line:84%
It began in 1917
with the overthrow

00:51:12.240 --> 00:51:15.100 align:middle line:84%
by the Bolsheviks of the
czar of Russia, Alexander.

00:51:15.100 --> 00:51:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And ever since
that time, there's

00:51:16.730 --> 00:51:18.460 align:middle line:84%
been this dialectic
going on with

00:51:18.460 --> 00:51:21.920 align:middle line:84%
the nation-state capitalists
and Western civilization

00:51:21.920 --> 00:51:25.250 align:middle line:84%
against the socialists
in Eastern culture.

00:51:25.250 --> 00:51:27.510 align:middle line:84%
And the bottom line
is that as long

00:51:27.510 --> 00:51:31.530 align:middle line:84%
as the Cold War was going on,
the United States was never

00:51:31.530 --> 00:51:33.770 align:middle line:84%
going to reveal any
of the technology

00:51:33.770 --> 00:51:37.210 align:middle line:84%
that they had encountered
with the Roswell crash, OK?

00:51:37.210 --> 00:51:39.300 align:middle line:84%
And they were going to
try to weaponize it.

00:51:39.300 --> 00:51:41.810 align:middle line:84%
You know the old
saying, the Sufi saying,

00:51:41.810 --> 00:51:44.352 align:middle line:84%
when a pickpocket meets a saint,
all he sees are his pockets.

00:51:44.352 --> 00:51:45.151 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Rights.

00:51:45.151 --> 00:51:45.951 align:middle line:90%
Right. [LAUGHING]

00:51:45.951 --> 00:51:46.751 align:middle line:90%
>>SHEEHAN: OK?

00:51:46.751 --> 00:51:48.770 align:middle line:84%
And so coming at it
from that perspective,

00:51:48.770 --> 00:51:52.030 align:middle line:84%
that worldview, which is a
dialectical, confrontational

00:51:52.030 --> 00:51:56.780 align:middle line:84%
worldview, they perceive
these extraterrestrial people

00:51:56.780 --> 00:51:58.870 align:middle line:90%
as being a potential threat, OK?

00:51:58.870 --> 00:52:01.810 align:middle line:84%
And so their job--
it's their job assigned

00:52:01.810 --> 00:52:03.950 align:middle line:84%
by both the Republican
and Democratic Party.

00:52:03.950 --> 00:52:05.925 align:middle line:84%
Your job is to
protect the airspace

00:52:05.925 --> 00:52:08.300 align:middle line:84%
and not allow anyone to come
into the airspace that isn't

00:52:08.300 --> 00:52:09.340 align:middle line:90%
monitored and taken care of.

00:52:09.340 --> 00:52:11.230 align:middle line:84%
And here these people
are coming and going,

00:52:11.230 --> 00:52:12.230 align:middle line:90%
and we can't admit that.

00:52:12.230 --> 00:52:14.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But that could have
been a sell to the public.

00:52:14.340 --> 00:52:14.910 align:middle line:90%
Be afraid.

00:52:14.910 --> 00:52:15.690 align:middle line:90%
Be very afraid.

00:52:15.690 --> 00:52:16.380 align:middle line:90%
We need your money.

00:52:16.380 --> 00:52:17.050 align:middle line:90%
We're developing this stuff.

00:52:17.050 --> 00:52:19.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: Well, they were still
working on Russia at that time.

00:52:19.740 --> 00:52:21.281 align:middle line:84%
Because what they're
doing is they're

00:52:21.281 --> 00:52:24.280 align:middle line:84%
being able to fund at
that point $300 million

00:52:24.280 --> 00:52:27.020 align:middle line:84%
a year to protect
us against Russia.

00:52:27.020 --> 00:52:29.980 align:middle line:84%
And now they're into
doing anti-terrorism.

00:52:29.980 --> 00:52:33.280 align:middle line:84%
This big one, this
big one that we--

00:52:33.280 --> 00:52:35.520 align:middle line:84%
one of our major assignments
that all of us who

00:52:35.520 --> 00:52:40.910 align:middle line:84%
care about this is to
prevent the warrior class,

00:52:40.910 --> 00:52:43.220 align:middle line:84%
the national security
state people,

00:52:43.220 --> 00:52:45.970 align:middle line:84%
from making this
the ultimate other.

00:52:45.970 --> 00:52:48.090 align:middle line:84%
And these are the
ultimate other in that

00:52:48.090 --> 00:52:50.254 align:middle line:84%
we have to spend more
than $600 billion a year.

00:52:50.254 --> 00:52:52.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That was the
warning of Wernher von Braun.

00:52:52.420 --> 00:52:53.540 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That's exactly
right, that they'll

00:52:53.540 --> 00:52:55.600 align:middle line:84%
go right to the thing,
and so you've got

00:52:55.600 --> 00:52:57.120 align:middle line:90%
to stop them from doing that.

00:52:57.120 --> 00:53:00.077 align:middle line:84%
So you have to establish a
friendlier dynamic with regard

00:53:00.077 --> 00:53:01.160 align:middle line:90%
to the extraterrestrials--

00:53:01.160 --> 00:53:01.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which is
what you're doing.

00:53:01.710 --> 00:53:03.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: That's our
job, is to do that.

00:53:03.700 --> 00:53:05.290 align:middle line:90%
But-- so that's one thing.

00:53:05.290 --> 00:53:09.020 align:middle line:84%
That one, which is comparatively
predictable, at least for those

00:53:09.020 --> 00:53:12.760 align:middle line:84%
of us who spent 30, 40
years in this area, that's

00:53:12.760 --> 00:53:13.850 align:middle line:90%
one we have to be careful.

00:53:13.850 --> 00:53:17.610 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand,
Marshall Summers-- there's

00:53:17.610 --> 00:53:19.660 align:middle line:84%
a whole set of books
that have been written

00:53:19.660 --> 00:53:23.070 align:middle line:84%
by this fellow named Marshall
Summers, which is called

00:53:23.070 --> 00:53:25.060 align:middle line:90%
"The Allies of Humanity."

00:53:25.060 --> 00:53:27.270 align:middle line:84%
And what he's talking
about is the fact

00:53:27.270 --> 00:53:31.100 align:middle line:84%
that there are, in fact,
extraterrestrial civilizations

00:53:31.100 --> 00:53:34.050 align:middle line:84%
that are very spiritually
evolved and very

00:53:34.050 --> 00:53:37.030 align:middle line:84%
compassionate and supportive
of our human family here,

00:53:37.030 --> 00:53:39.240 align:middle line:84%
very concerned about
what it is we're

00:53:39.240 --> 00:53:41.350 align:middle line:84%
doing to the planet,
the destruction

00:53:41.350 --> 00:53:45.490 align:middle line:84%
of the natural environment, that
this is an extraordinarily--

00:53:45.490 --> 00:53:48.980 align:middle line:84%
not unique planet, but it's
a very rare type of planet

00:53:48.980 --> 00:53:51.687 align:middle line:84%
that gestates life,
that generates life.

00:53:51.687 --> 00:53:53.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The diversity of life.

00:53:53.020 --> 00:53:54.790 align:middle line:84%
>>SHEEHAN: The vast
diversity of life.

00:53:54.790 --> 00:53:58.610 align:middle line:84%
And it's an absolutely
fabulous experience.

00:53:58.610 --> 00:54:02.240 align:middle line:84%
But there's only one in every
like 5,000 to 10,000 planets

00:54:02.240 --> 00:54:03.620 align:middle line:90%
that has this capacity.

00:54:03.620 --> 00:54:06.610 align:middle line:84%
So this quest we're
on of these exoplanets

00:54:06.610 --> 00:54:09.820 align:middle line:84%
that we're looking for, there's
probably 50 billion of them

00:54:09.820 --> 00:54:12.580 align:middle line:84%
that they assume are
within the Goldilocks zone.

00:54:12.580 --> 00:54:14.520 align:middle line:84%
But there's very
few of them that

00:54:14.520 --> 00:54:18.210 align:middle line:84%
are of this nature in
that we, as the custodians

00:54:18.210 --> 00:54:21.500 align:middle line:84%
of this particular planet,
this particular species, Homo

00:54:21.500 --> 00:54:25.290 align:middle line:84%
